gomodel:SYNGO_2211  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099699 replaced by GO:0097060" , "Rationale: ITGB1 was localized in synapses of hippocampal neurons.\n\n16/01/2018 Pim\n- The experimental data in Fig.1f does not resolve the plasma membrane of the synapse. The localization of ITGB1 to the plasma membrane is inferred from the known membrane localization of the protein and the effectiveness of extracellular inhibitors of ITGB1 that perturbe actin-dynamics in the dendritic spine (only possible when the ITGB1 is TM-plasma membrane protein).. Experimental description: Materials and Methods\nHIPPOCAMPAL NEURON CULTURE, TRANSFECTION.\nCultures of hippocampal neurons were prepared from embryonic day 15 (E15) to E16 mouse embryos." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2211" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

